                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d534">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9659: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-25T21:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 25, 1937—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>181. Your unnumbered [<hi rend="italic">514</hi>,] August 24, 8 p.m. Please
                    inform Department what is the “Davidson neutral zone plan” and give your
                    comments on each of the two statements made in the second sentence of the quoted
                    message communicated in your telegram under reference.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
